<div class="aboutCopy">
    <h2>The Tzolk'in</h2>
    <p>
The Tzolk'in is a sacred ritual cycle of 260 days, and consists of a number paired with a day-glyph. Each day, both the number and the sign increment; the number resets after 13 cycles while the day resets after 20 cycles; so, for instance, <i> 1 Ajaw </i> is followed by <i> 2 Imix</i>, which is followed by <i>3 Ik'</i>, and so forth until <i>13 Eb'</i>, which is followed by <i>1 B'en</i>. The same pair of number and sign will therefore only repeat every 260 days.
    </p>
</div>

